Patch target: dist/mcp/client.js

Problem: ensureServersInitialized() does a dynamic import of
'../mcp/config' with no file extension. Node's ESM resolver requires
explicit extensions on relative imports and rejects this outright with
ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND. This exception was caught by an outer .catch(() => {})
in the original getAllGrokTools() (see patch 02), so it failed completely
silently — no MCP server ever actually initialized in the chat/agent loop,
even though the standalone `grok mcp test` / `grok mcp list` commands
(which apparently go through a different code path) reported the server as
healthy. This is the root cause; patch 02 alone does not fix anything until
this import actually resolves.

--- a/dist/mcp/client.js
+++ b/dist/mcp/client.js
@@ (inside ensureServersInitialized(), ~line 113)
-        const { loadMCPConfig } = await import('../mcp/config');
+        const { loadMCPConfig } = await import('../mcp/config.js');

After this fix, expect the first MCP-tool-using headless call to take
15-20+ seconds on a cold start (spawning the MCP server subprocess,
completing its handshake, listing its tools) before the actual chat
completion request goes out. That's expected, not a hang — give it a
generous timeout rather than assuming it's stuck.
